{{Politics of Rwanda}}
A '''constitutional referendum''' was held in [[Rwanda]] on 26 May 2003. The [[Constitution of Rwanda|new constitution]] created a presidential republic with a [[Bicameralism|bicameral]] [[Parliament of Rwanda|parliament]], and banned the incitement of racial hatred. It was approved by 93% of voters with a 90% voter turnout.<ref>[http://africanelections.tripod.com/rw.html Elections in Rwanda] African Elections Database</ref> Following its approval, [[Rwandan presidential election, 2003|presidential elections]] were held on 25 August and [[Rwandan parliamentary election, 2003|parliamentary elections]] on 29-30 September.
